item.title: How much does lipo cost?
item.dc:creator: @Yz85Racer Yz85Racer
item.description:
@Yz85Racer wrote:

[quote=“maniown, post:26, topic:256584”][quote author=the fu superior link=topic=338897.msg2628778#msg2628778 date=1231986336]

I suggest anorexia first.

That would make myself hungry again.

I’m 19, 115lbs, 5’ 7" and I eat all day.

I’m hungry every 15 minutes.

115 after you drain your blood?

Shut up fatty.

Do it the healthy way, man up and fucking run.

Your dreams include sitting on a motorcycle and going in circles. You’re more lazy than I am.
[/quote] ROFL Riding a dirtbike is a huge workout.[/quote]
Agreed, it’s not as easy as people think.

  1. You’re constantly doing squats, every 2 or so seconds, so it owns your legs.
  2. You’re having to hang onto the bike and keep straight and fluid, while it’s trying to chuck you.
  3. You’re forever eating huge stones in the nose/chest etc.
  4. You’ve got to do it with 40 other people, all riding to their full potential. So, you’re full of adrenaline, which usually cuts your fitness in half.
  5. You have to usually do it 3 times a race, for 30 minutes + 2 laps.
  6. And you’re always lifting the bike, with your legs and arms.

I could be here all day, but I’m over trying to defend it. I just find it ironic people think you sit on a bike and twist the throttle, funny how the sports university (can’t remember the name, google it) found it be the 2nd hardest sport, behind boxing. And boxing is just, boxing. No better way to put it.
